## Background and Motivation

When examining symbols it would be helpful to understand if an attribute is reserved and only meant to be used by the compiler.

## Proposed API
```diff
namespace Microsoft.CodeAnalysis
{
     public class AttributeData
     {
+        public bool IsReserved { get; }
     }
```

## Usage Examples
Omitting reserved attributes when dumping attributes applied to a member.
``` C#
foreach (var attribute in symbol.GetAttributes())
{
    if (!attribute.IsReserved}
    {
        WriteAttribute(attribute);
    }
}
```

## Alternative Designs
We can hardcode our own list, but it will get out of date as new language features create new attributes.

